An Act preserve license plate actionable toll enforcement and safety.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 6 of chapter 90 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the second sentence the following
3 sentence:- The No said number plates nor any part thereof shall not be covered or obscured with
4 any opaque, transparent, translucent or tinted material.
5 SECTION 2. Said section 6 of said chapter 90, as so appearing, is hereby further
6 amended by adding the following paragraph:-
7 If a law enforcement officer observes that a number plate is covered or obscured by an
8 opaque, transparent, translucent or tinted material, the officer may stop the motor vehicle and
9 issue the violator a citation.
10 SECTION 3. Section 7A of said chapter 90, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
11 inserting after the word “plates”, in line 38, the following words:- ; provided, that any number
