12 plate covered or obscured by an opaque, transparent, translucent or tinted material shall be an
13 improper and unsafe condition.
14 SECTION 4. Section 7V of said chapter 90, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
15 inserting after the word “seven A”, in line 15, the following words:- ; and the requirement that
16 motor vehicles be issued a certificate of rejection for failing to comply with the prohibition in
17 section 6 against covering or obscuring a number plate with an opaque, transparent, translucent
18 or tinted material.
19 SECTION 5. Section 2 shall take effect 2 years following the passage of this act.
